150 grams Jasmine Rice
240 grams British Beef Mince
80 grams Mangetout
80 grams Sliced Mushrooms
48 grams Sweet Chilli Sauce
30 grams Peanut Butter
25 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
1 sachet(s) Indonesian Style Spice Mix
5 grams Roasted White Sesame Seeds
100 milliliter(s) Boiled Water for the Sauce

Boil a half-full kettle.
Pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 12-13 mins.
Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Cover and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince, mangetout and mushrooms, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the sweet chilli, peanut butter, soy and boiled water (see pantry).
Add the Indonesian style spice mix and sauce to the pan.
Simmer, 1-2 mins.
Add a splash of water if it's looking a little thick.

Share the rice between your bowls.
Top with the beef stir-fry.
Sprinkle over the sesame seeds.
Enjoy!